一位中小企业主的复工守望：一边是焦虑，一边是信心。
A small and medium-sized business owner back to work watchful: anxiety on one side, confidence on the other.
张锐2020-02-13 15:40。
Zhang Rui 2020-02-13 15: 40.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察报 记者 张锐 广州报道刘闽江一面觉得两难，一面又跑前跑后地准备申请复工的材料。
Zhang Rui Guangzhou, a reporter for the Economic Observer, while reporting on Liu Minjiang, felt a dilemma as he raced back and forth to apply for materials to resume work.
。
.
“总会过去的，是吧。
"" It will pass, won't it?
”他告诉记者，现在开工其实没什么订单需求，只是为维持生产能力，稳定人心。
He told reporters that there was no demand for orders to start work, just to maintain production capacity and reassure people.
往年这个时候，他和工人已经开始为三、四月的订单加班，但今年他做的更多的是在员工群里提醒大家暂时不要返工，注意防护。
At this time of the year, he and his workers had been working overtime for orders for March and April, but this year he was more likely to warn employees not to rework and take precautions.
。
.
尽管他深知如果新型冠状病毒疫情再持续两三个月，自己可能也没地方“找钱”，但依然相信在那之前事情会解决的。
Although he knows that if the new coronavirus outbreak continues for another two or three months, he may not have a place to "change money," but he believes things will work out before then.
他反复提到“有信心”。
He repeated the words "have confidence."
。
.
刘闽江的这番话与此前魅KTV投资人、桔子水晶酒店创始人吴海在其个人微信号中发表的《哎，我只是个做中小微企业的》是相似的。
Liu's comments are similar to those of Wu Hai, founder of the Crystal Orange Hotel and a former KTV investor, in his personal microsignal.
吴海称，只要疫情能解决，时间可以修复一切信心问题。
'If the outbreak can be resolved, time can fix any confidence problems, 'Mr. Wu said.
政府不用操心市场信心问题，要做的工作是争取帮“我们”活到那一天。
The government doesn't have to worry about confidence in the market. All it has to do is try to help "us" live to that day.
。
.
2月6日，清华大学经济管理学院金融系教授朱武祥、北京大学汇丰商学院管理学教授魏炜等学者联合调研发布《疫情对中小企业的影响及应对思考》调查显示，31.08%的企业预计 2020年营业收入下降幅度超过 50%，58.88%的企业下降 20%以上。
On February 6, 2007, Zhu Wuxiang, professor of finance at Tsinghua University School of Economics and Wei Wei, professor of management at HSBC Business School of Peking University, said 31.08 percent of enterprises expected their business revenue to fall by more than 50 percent in 2020 and 58.88 percent by more than 20 percent.
同时，35.96%的企业只能维持 1 个月，能维持 6 个月及以上的企业只有 9.27%。
At the same time, 35.96 per cent of enterprises lasted only one month and only 9.27 per cent were able to sustain six months or more.
如果疫情持续半年以上，90%的企业很可能歇业或者破产。
If the epidemic continues for more than six months, 90% of businesses are likely to close or go bankrupt.
。
.
一波未平一波又起。
Waves of water rose again and again.
刘闽江是广东一家制造音响的小型民企的老板，早些年曾为国际大牌代工，如今在广州和佛山各有一个工厂，产品一半在国内销售，一半销往国外。
LiuMin Jiang, the owner of a small private enterprise that manufactures acoustics in Guangdong, worked as an international agent in the past few years, and now has a factory in Guangzhou and Foshan.
无论是业务发展、生产规模，刘闽江和他的公司在广东都是极其普通的。
Whether business development, production scale, Liu Min Jiang and his company in Guangdong are extremely common.
。
.
今年1月中旬，广东省统计局正式公布数据，2019年广东地区生产总值总量达10.7万亿元，按可比价格计算，比上年增长6.2%，完成6%-6.5%的年度预期目标。
In mid-January, the Guangdong Provincial Bureau of Statistics officially announced that the gross domestic product (GDP) of 2019 reached 10.7 trillion yuan, 6.2% higher than the previous year at comparable prices, fulfilling the annual target of 6% - 6.5%.
在中国第一经济大省率先迈上十万亿的台阶背后，大量刘闽江这样的中小民企主，在面临多重压力的背景下贡献了增长力量。
Back in China's largest economy province, where hundreds of billions of people have taken the lead, a large number of small and medium-sized enterprises, such as Liu Minjiang, have contributed to growth in the face of multiple pressures.
。
.
2020年春节前，刘闽江这样的企业思考着从广州到周边偏远城市，工厂一路搬迁、环保审核愈发严格，以及中美贸易背景下外贸形势不断变化的问题。
Before the 2020 Spring Festival, companies like Liu Minjiang are thinking about moving factories from Guangzhou to outlying cities, tougher environmental audits and changing foreign trade in the context of China-US trade.
现在，突袭而来的疫情，让他们在新一年的生产经营中必须要面临新的压力。
Now, the sudden outbreak of the disease, let them in the new year's production and management must face new pressure.
。
.
1月28日，《广东省人民政府关于企业复工和学校开学时间的通知》下发。
On January 28, the Circular of the People's Government of Guangdong Province Concerning the Resumption of Work and School Opening Hours was issued.
通知要求，除五类特殊行业外，各类企业复工时间不早于2月9日24时，并对返粤人员的疫情防控工作进行严格要求。
The notice requires enterprises to resume work no earlier than 2400 hours on 9 February, in addition to the five special industries, and imposes strict requirements for the prevention and control of the disease among personnel returning to Guangdong.
同一时间，全国其他城市也出台了类似的规定，各地跨省公共交通不同程度被切断。
At the same time, other cities across the country have introduced similar rules, and public transport across provinces has been cut off to varying degrees.
。
.
延迟复工、跨省交通管制以及异地返回员工隔离14天等疫情防控措施陆续公布，对于刘闽江这样的企业主而言是措手不及的。
Delays in resuming work, cross-provincial traffic control and 14 days of isolation of returning workers have been announced, which has taken entrepreneurs like Liu Min Jiang by surprise.
根据广东省人民政府2019年数据统计的就业数据，广东约有3000万外来务工人员。
According to 2019 statistics from the Guangdong Provincial People's Government, Guangdong has about 30 million migrant workers.
。
.
1月24日前，大量的外来务工人员已经陆续离开广东，回家过春节。
By January 24, a large number of migrant workers had left Guangdong for the Spring Festival.
“很多员工都是广西、湖南、四川的，节前回去，本地可以复工的大概只有三分之一，很多都是这样的情况。
"Many of the employees are from Guangxi, Hunan and Sichuan. Only about one-third of the local workers can return to work before the festival.
”刘闽江说，与互联网企业可以远程办公不同，他们这样的企业是难以开展线上业务的，而全国各地娱乐场所停止营业更是直接造成了音响产品的销售几近停滞。
Unlike Internet companies, which can telecommute, it is difficult for companies like them to do business online, says Mr Liu, whose sales of stereo products have come to a near standstill as entertainment venues across the country cease to operate.
。
.
一边是焦虑一边是信心。
One is anxiety and the other is confidence.
2月6日，清华大学经济管理学院金融系教授朱武祥、北京大学汇丰商学院管理学教授魏炜等学者联合调研发布《疫情对中小企业的影响及应对思考》一文，对全国多地 1435 家中小企业进行调查显示，75.62%的企业2019年营业收入在5000万元以下，9.34%的企业营业收入在5000-9999 万元，营收 1 亿元以下的企业合计占比 84.94%，营业收入不超过 6 亿元的企业占 98.39%。
On February 6, 2007, Zhu Wuxiang, professor of finance at Tsinghua University School of Economics and Wei Wei, a professor of management at HSBC Business School of Peking University, conducted a survey of 1,435 small and medium-sized enterprises in different parts of the country.
。
.
从疫情对公司的营收影响来看，31.08%的企业估计疫情导致 2020 年营业收入下降幅度超过 50%，27.80%的 企业预计营业收入下降 20-50%，合计 58.88%的企业 2020 年营业收入下降 20% 以上。
In terms of the impact of the epidemic on the company's revenues, 31.08 per cent of the enterprises estimated that the epidemic had led to a decline of more than 50 per cent in business revenues in 2020, 27.80 per cent of enterprises expected a decline of 20 to 50 per cent, and a total of 58.88 per cent of enterprises experienced a decline of more than 20 per cent in 2020.
。
.
而根据企业账上现金余额能维持企业生存的时间调查显示，35.96%的企业只能维持 1 个月，31.92%的企业可以维持 2 个月，17.03%的企业可以维持 3 个月，能维持 6 个月及以上的企业只有 9.27%。
According to the survey, 35.96 per cent of enterprises can survive for only one month, 31.92 per cent for two months, 17.03 per cent for three months and 9.27 per cent for six months or more.
。
.
以刘闽江的自我评估来看，他是前述占比17.03%的企业当中的一个。
Judging by Liu's self-assessment, he is one of 17.03 per cent of the aforementioned enterprises.
他在准备复工，就在他准备复工的时间里，知名餐饮企业西贝莜面村春节前后损失7、8亿、新潮传媒宣布裁员500人等新闻穿插在疫情新闻之间。
He is preparing to resume work, just when he is ready to resume work, well-known catering enterprises Xibei naked oats around the Spring Festival losses around the loss of 700, 800 million, trendy media announced 500 layoffs, and other news interspersed with the epidemic news.
。
.
2月6日，广东省政府正式印发《关于应对新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎疫情支持企业复工复产的若干政策措施》，要求全力支持和推动受疫情影响的各类企业复工复产。
On February 6, the Guangdong Provincial Government officially issued the Policy Measures to Support the Reactivation of Enterprises due to Pneumonia due to New Coronavirus Infection, calling for full support and promotion for the resumption of work of enterprises affected by the epidemic.
但这对于很多中小企而言，只是政策性的复工。
But for many small and medium-sized enterprises, this is just a policy return to work.
。
.
2月9日，刘闽江先后向广州、佛山当地政府部门提交了复工的资料。
On February 9, Liu Min Jiang submitted information on the resumption of work to local government departments in Guangzhou and Foshan.
“广州这边的效率比较高，第二天我就收到了回复允许开工，但佛山因为是在工业园区，审批程序感觉还要更严格，目前还没有确切的时间。
"It was more efficient on this side of Guangzhou, and the next day I received a reply allowing work to start, but Foshan felt more stringent because it was in the industrial park and there was no definite time frame.
”。
"
但开工并不意味着一切恢复常态，刘闽江带着不足一半的工人忙活的是年前剩下的订单，国内目前的市场需求没有恢复。
But starting work doesn't mean everything is back to normal. With less than half the workers on his hands, Mr. Liu is working on orders left over from a year ago.
他现在做的更多的是疫情防控，每天在群里提醒员工最新的疫情消息，和一些防护注意事项。
He is now doing more disease control, alerting staff in the group to the latest outbreaks and precautions.
这些工作他还要截图上传给监管部门备份，以表示企业在开展防疫工作。
He also sent a screenshot of the work to regulatory authorities to back up, to show that the enterprise is carrying out epidemic prevention.
“国外的客户最近问的是我们恢复得怎么样，能不能开工，能做多少。
"Foreign clients have recently asked us how well we are doing, whether we can get to work and how much we can do.
”。
"
根据前述北大、清华两位学者的调查结果，疫情影响期间，员工工资和五险一金占 59.79%，租金 16.59%，两项合计 76.38%。
According to the above-mentioned findings of the two scholars, 59.79% of the staff wages and five risks were paid, 16.59% were rented and 76.38% was spent on both items during the epidemic.
说明多数中小企业员工薪资和五险一金是成本支出的大头，其次是租金，偿还贷款占 13.45%，三项合计占 89.83%。
This means that most SME employees' salaries and insurance premiums are the largest part of the cost, followed by rent, with 13.45 per cent of loans repaid and three out of 89.83 per cent.
。
.
“这事情肯定会过去的，但着急也没办法。
"It will certainly pass away, but there is nothing to be done about it.
”刘闽江说。
"said Liu.
另一位在广州的企业负责人则向记者表示，由公司的口罩、测温仪设备不足，选择短期内不开工，但并没有太大的人员变动计划。
Another head of the company in Guangzhou told reporters that the company by the mask, thermometer equipment is insufficient, choose not to start work in the short term, but there are no major staff changes planned.
“现在园区租金和银行贷款的问题还没有直接压力，没有催，收到的信号还是比较积极，愿意减免。
"Right now, there is no direct pressure on the rent and bank loans, there is no rush, the signal received is more positive, willing to reduce."
”。
"
